Data

We consider three different model specifications. M1: Correctly specified: 8 covariates, 2 interactions and one quadratic effect M2: Almost correctly specified: 8 covariates, 1 interaction; missing 1 interaction and quadratic effect M3: Incorrectly specified: only 6 covariates; missing 2 covariates, 2 interactions and quadratic effect

load("Data/Scenario2/Sim_Dat_Training.RData")
load("Data/Scenario2/Sim_Dat_Validation.RData")

# true coefficients 
load("Data/Scenario2/True_beta.RData")
# beta data frame
beta_df <- data.frame(Coef = c("(Intercept)", 
                               "X1", "X2", "X3", "X4", "X5", "X6", "X7", "X8",
                               "I(X5^2)", 
                               "X1:X2", "X3:X4"),
                      True = beta_vector)

model_scenario2 <- list(c("Y ~ 1 + X1 + X2 + X3 + X4 + X5 + X6 + X7 + X8 + X1 * X2 + X3 * X4 + X5^2"),
                        c("Y ~ 1 + X1 + X2 + X3 + X4 + X5 + X6 + X7 + X8 + X1 * X2"),
                        c("Y ~ 1 + X1 + X2 + X3 + X4 + X5 + X6"))

# training design matrix 
Xdesign1_train <- train_dat_df %>% select(-Y)
Xdesign2_train <- train_dat_df %>%  select(-c("X34", "X5sq", "Y"))
Xdesign3_train <- train_dat_df %>%  select(c("Intercept", 
                                             "X1", "X2", "X3", "X4", "X5", "X6"))


# validation design matrix 
Xdesign1_val <- val_dat_df %>% select(-Y)
Xdesign2_val <- val_dat_df %>%  select(-c("X34", "X5sq", "Y"))
Xdesign3_val <- val_dat_df %>%  select(c("Intercept", 
                                             "X1", "X2", "X3", "X4", "X5", "X6"))

M1: ML

ML_mod <- loadRData(fileName = "Cluster_results/Scenario2/Model1/ML_model.RData")

# model coefficients
ML_mod_coef <- summary(ML_mod)$coef %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  mutate(Coef = rownames(summary(ML_mod)$coef)) %>% 
  left_join(beta_df, by = "Coef")

list_coefficients[["ML_CMS"]] <- ggplot(data = ML_mod_coef,
                                        aes(x = Coef,
                                            y = Estimate)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = Estimate - 1.96 * `Std. Error`,
                    ymax = Estimate + 1.96 * `Std. Error`)) +
  geom_point(aes(y = True,
                 color = "True coefficient"),
             shape = 4, size = 3) +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(legend.position = "bottom") +
  labs(x = "Model coefficient",
       color = "",
       caption = "ML estimation, correct") +
  coord_flip()

# values for training data
AUC_train_ML <- roc(train_dat_df$Y, ML_mod$fitted.values)$auc
## Setting levels: control = 0, case = 1
## Setting direction: controls < cases
ECE_train_ML <- mean(abs(train_dat_df$Y - ML_mod$fitted.value))
Brier_train_ML <- mean((train_dat_df$Y - ML_mod$fitted.value)^2)

ML_CMS_train_performance <- data.frame(AUC = AUC_train_ML,
                                       ECE = ECE_train_ML, 
                                       Brier = Brier_train_ML)

# predict probabilities for validation data
val_dat_df$pred <- predict(ML_mod,
                           newdata = val_dat_df,
                           type = "response")


# calibration plot
list_calibration_plots[["ML_CMS"]] <- calibrationPlot(data = val_dat_df,
                                                      caption = "ML estimation, correct")

# ROC
list_ROC[["ML_CMS"]] <- ROCplot(val_dat_df$Y, val_dat_df$pred, 
                                caption = "ML estimation, correct")
## Setting levels: control = 0, case = 1
## Setting direction: controls < cases
# AUC 
list_AUC[["ML_CMS"]] <- roc(val_dat_df$Y, val_dat_df$pred)$auc
## Setting levels: control = 0, case = 1
## Setting direction: controls < cases
# ECE / Brier score
list_ECE[["ML_CMS"]] <- ECE(val_dat_df$Y, val_dat_df$pred)
list_Brier[["ML_CMS"]] <- Brier(val_dat_df$Y, val_dat_df$pred)

M1: Rankboost

Rankboost is implemented via XGBoost by (1) fitting a logistic regression model and optimizing for the AUC and (2) optimizing for pairwise concordance (identical to AUC interpretation).

XG_mod <- loadRData(fileName = "Cluster_results/Scenario2/Model1/XG_model.RData")

# Predict and evaluate AUC on validation data
val_dat_df$pred <- predict(XG_mod, Xdesign1_val %>% 
                         select(-Intercept) %>% 
                         as.matrix())
# predictions contains the predicted probabilities for class 1

# calibration plot 
list_calibration_plots[["XBoost_CMS"]] <- calibrationPlot(data = val_dat_df,
                                                   caption = "AUC Rankboost, correct")
# ROC
list_ROC[["XBoost_CMS"]] <- ROCplot(val_dat_df$Y, val_dat_df$pred, 
                                caption = "AUC Rankboost, correct")
## Setting levels: control = 0, case = 1
## Setting direction: controls < cases
# estimate AUC
list_AUC[["XBoost_CMS"]] <- roc(val_dat_df$Y, val_dat_df$pred)$auc
## Setting levels: control = 0, case = 1
## Setting direction: controls < cases
# ECE / Brier score
list_ECE[["XBoost_CMS"]] <- ECE(val_dat_df$Y, val_dat_df$pred)
list_Brier[["XBoost_CMS"]] <- Brier(val_dat_df$Y, val_dat_df$pred)

# Rankbased only

                         select(-Intercept) %>% 
                         as.matrix())
# predictions contains the predicted probabilities for class 1

# calibration plot

                                                   caption = "AUC Rankboost (rank), correct")
# ROC
list_ROC[["XBoost_rank_CMS"]] <- ROCplot(val_dat_df$Y, val_dat_df$pred, 
                                caption = "AUC Rankboost (rank), correct")
## Setting levels: control = 0, case = 1
## Setting direction: controls < cases
# estimate AUC

## Setting levels: control = 0, case = 1
## Setting direction: controls < cases

list_ECE[["XBoost_rank_CMS"]] <- ECE(val_dat_df$Y, val_dat_df$pred)

coef_VICMS <- ML_mod_coef %>% 
                     select(Coef, True, Estimate) %>% 
                     rename(ML = Estimate) %>% 
  left_join(AUC_NM_beta, by = "Coef")

val_dat_df$pred <- predict_for_beta(Xdesign = Xdesign3_val %>% 
                                      as.matrix(),
                                    beta = AUC_NM_beta$AUC_NM)

# calibration plot
list_calibration_plots[["AUC_NM_VICMS"]] <- calibrationPlot(data = val_dat_df,
                                                   caption = "AUC NM, very incorrect")


# ROC

                             caption = "AUC NM, very incorrect")
## Setting levels: control = 0, case = 1
## Setting direction: controls < cases
# AUC

## Setting levels: control = 0, case = 1

We compare the coefficients. “True” pertains to the coefficient value for simulation. It is not the “true” coefficient the misspecified logistic regression converges to, i.e. the value that minimizes the Kullback-Leibler distance between the incorrectly and correctly parametrized probability distribution.

# coefficient estimates for correct and incorrect model specification
coef_CMS$Type <- "correct model specification"
coef_ICMS$Type <- "incorrect model specification"
coef_VICMS$Type <- "very incorrect model specification"

coef_df <- rbind(coef_CMS, 
                 coef_ICMS, 
                 coef_VICMS) %>% 
  gather(key = "Estimation", 
         value = "Value", 
         -c("Coef", "Type"))


# plot coefficient estimation for all methods
# for correct and incorrect model specification
ggplot(data = coef_df %>% filter(Estimation != "True"),
       aes(x = Coef,
           y = Value,
           color = Estimation)) +
  geom_point(position = position_jitter(width = 0.2, height = 0)) +
  geom_point(data = coef_df %>% filter(Estimation == "True"), 
             aes(y = Value,
                 color = "True"),
             shape = 4, size = 3) +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(legend.position = "bottom") +
  labs(x = "Model coefficient",
       color = "", shape = "") +
  coord_flip() +
  facet_grid(~ Type, 
             scales = "free")
